@node Introduction "RestoreQuietness v1.0 Documentation"

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
The Q command in AmiExpress and SigmaExpress is used to make a node quiet
(invisible to other nodes). But these BBS programs (maybe not the latest
SigmaExpress?) have a bug - they don't restore the nodes' "quietness" when
the user logs out, not even when the next user logs in! RestoreQuietness
fixes this problem. It restores the node's quietness to what it originally
was (when the node was started by ACP) - quiet or not quiet.
@endnode

@node Usage "RestoreQuietness v1.0 Documentation"

Usage
~~~~~
RestoreQuietness is not a door. It is a utility that should be run from
the logoff scripts. It requires one argument: the node number.

Let's say you put the tool in your C: directory. Insert the following line
*last* in the logoff scripts:

C:RestoreQuietness <node>

For example, in the logoff script for node 3 the last line should look
like this:

C:RestoreQuietness 3

Why the *last* line?! Well, if the user wants to be quiet (or not quiet)
when he logs off he should remain so as long as possible during the
logoff.

This tool can be made resident even though I don't see the point in doing
so - it is very small and is loaded in no-time.
@endnode

